<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                        <head><persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-13"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 13, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I had yesterday afternoon the honor to
                            receive your note of the same day communicating to me intelligence which
                            you had received from the United States consul general at Montreal,
                            respecting a gathering of enemies of the United States at Windsor, in
                            Canada. I immediately transmitted the intelligence to the governor
                            general at that province.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>LYONS. </signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>